It doesn't have to be expensive at all! I use it a lot on my pets or myself and mostly straight from an atomizer 30ml spray bottle, which doesn't need topping up very often. (Plus I make it myself, so it doesn't really cost a lot once you've got the equipment)

Good point about the door handles

@werxeh8027 low and high are relative terms. What matters here is the rate of electrolisys and the rate of mixing.  

A low rate of electrolisys and high rate of mixing would not be favorable to co2  comming out of solution.

 On the other hand low mixing and high rate of electrolisys (high currents driven by high voltage or high surface area), would tend to favor the evolution of co2 from the solution. Membranes serve to minimize mixing.
